I think the problem is with your SQL configuration object When specifying instance name along with host, config should be something as below:

    var config = {
            user: &#39;sa&#39;,
            password: &#39;Password13&#39;,
            server: &#39;localhost\\instancename&#39;,
            database: &#39;hellodb&#39;  
        }; 
Alternatively you can pass instance details as options parameter:

    var config = {
            user: &#39;sa&#39;,
            password: &#39;Password13&#39;,
            server: &#39;localhost&#39;,
            database: &#39;hellodb&#39;,
            options: {
                instanceName: &quot;instance name&quot;   
            }
        };

You made 2 mistakes in config obj:

 1. The server parameter should be as `localhost\\instance` not `localhost/instance` when the instance details passed along with the server.
 2. it&#39;s `options` not `option` in config obj.
 
 Further reading: https://tediousjs.github.io/node-mssql/#connect-callback

